The Great Wall of China is one of the most iconic and recognizable landmarks in the world, with a rich history that spans over 2,000 years. Its construction began during the Warring States period (475-221 BCE) and continued through the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644 CE), making it one of the longest walls ever built.

The Great Wall served multiple purposes throughout its history, including military defense, border control, and trade regulation

The Apollo 11 mission, launched on July 16, 1969, was a significant milestone in space exploration history. It marked the first time humans set foot on the Moon. The spacecraft, consisting of the Command Module "Columbia" and the Lunar Module "Eagle," carried astronauts Neil Armstrong, Buzz Aldrin, and Michael Collins.
